  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promotion of a Global Arms Trade Treaty (restricted Dutch Government)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this programme of work is to promote a global Arms Trade Treaty, which will prevent irresponsible international conventional arms transfers in order to prevent their harmful consequences.  Too many civilians are killed, injured, displaced or impoverished due to armed violence and the Arms Trade Treaty is one essential element to reduce this human toll.  Oxfam proposes to work alongside other partners to undertake work around three areas:    1 Developing knowledge and expertise on the implementation of an Arms Trade Treaty   2 Multi -media/digital media activities   3 Activities to develop supporter actions  - with a focus on Africa.</narrative>
  </description>
